solution: ```class Solution {
    public String greatestLetter(String s) {
        boolean[] lower = new boolean[26];
        boolean[] upper = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') lower[c - 'a'] = true;
            else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') upper[c - 'A'] = true;
        }
        for (int i = 25; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (lower[i] && upper[i]) return String.valueOf((char)('A' + i));
        }
        return "";
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass to mark presence of each letter in both cases, then scan backwards from 'Z' to 'A' to find the first letter with both cases present. Uses only two fixed-size boolean arrays.

